FuncDef: The license delete command deletes a specified license file in the $_license directory.

ParaDef.Info:
Specifies the name of the license file to be deleted.
The value is a string of 1 to 127 case-sensitive characters without spaces.If the name of the license file to be deleted contains only a file name, the license files with this name are deleted from the
$_license directories on the master and slave main control boards in all chassis. If the name of the license file to be deleted contains a complete path, the license file only in this path is deleted.

Examples: Warning: The contents of file cfcard:/$_license/license.dat cannot be recycled. Continue? [Y/N]:y
ExtraInfo:
Usage Scenario
To delete unwanted or useless license files in the $_license directory, run the license delete command.
Prerequisites
Unwanted or useless license files are available in the $_license directory.
Precautions
In VS mode, this command is supported only by the admin VS.
